This function will return <tt>true</tt> if the year component of the given datetime value is a leap year or <tt>false</tt> otherwise. This can be a handy function for things like Easter Eggs in your games, or for unlocking special content.
The above code will check the current datetime to see if the year is a leap year or not. If it is it sets a global variable.
